AI-powered compiler error explanation via generateObject

Implementation:
1. tools/explain-error.ts - TypeScript tool using Vercel AI SDK
2. Schema: { summary: string, cause: string, fix?: string, relevant_lines?: number[] }
3. Graceful degradation: no API key → exit 1 → compiler prints raw error

Testing non-deterministic AI output:
- Don't check exact text
- Verify schema fields are populated
- Verify response mentions key terms ("NonexistentType", "undefined", etc.)
- Use AI to validate AI: generateObject({ schema: TestValidation })

This is part of the larger pattern:
- Compiler errors → AI explains
- Test failures → AI analyzes
- Commits → AI summarizes (already working in korulang_org!)
- Every friction point → generateObject with structured schema
